@startuml
title Local multi-region failover simulator (Docker)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam wrapWidth 200
skinparam maxMessageSize 120

legend left
  == Roles ==
  - "primary": pg_is_in_recovery() = false
  - "standby": pg_is_in_recovery() = true

  == Important behavior ==
  - Single-writer model: only one region should accept writes at a time
  - Replication is async: Region A -> Region B WAL streaming
  - Infra telemetry is NOT on the critical path (background only)
  - After promotion, Region B becomes primary and replication stops (regions may diverge)
endlegend

package "Client" {
  actor User
}

package "Docker network: regions" {
  component "ui\nNext.js (3000)" as UI
  component "ui API routes\nNext.js server (3000)\n(/api/* proxies)" as UIR
  component "router\nLB simulation (8090)" as LB
  component "api\nFastAPI (8080)" as API
  component "failover-controller" as FC
  component "infra\nDocker stats (7070)\n(cached, best-effort)" as INFRA

  database "Region A\npostgres-primary\n(5432)" as DBA
  database "Region B\npostgres-replica\n(5432)" as DBB
}

User --> UI : browser
UI --> UIR : fetch /api/dashboard,\n/api/write,\n/api/read
User --> LB : curl /write,/read,/status (optional)
UIR --> LB : HTTP proxy (sync)
LB --> API : forwards HTTP

note on link UIR --> LB
  Synchronous data path:
  UI waits for response
end note

API --> DBA : SQL write/read\n(when active=region-a)
API --> DBB : SQL read/write\n(when active=region-b)

DBA ..> DBB : WAL streaming replication\n(primary -> standby)
note on link DBA ..> DBB
  Async: replica visibility is eventual
end note

FC --> API : poll /decision or /status
FC --> DBB : docker exec pg_ctl promote\n(only on failover)
FC --> API : POST /admin/switch?region=region-b

UIR ..> INFRA : GET /api/infra\n(background, non-blocking)
note on link UIR ..> INFRA
  Observability only:
  MUST NOT block rows/status updates
end note

@enduml

